The Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) has disclosed that there are now 5,255 confirmed cases of Coronavirus (COVID-19) in 47 countries across Africa. The health agency also said Coronavirus death cases in Africa have increased to 172. According to Africa CDC, there are 371 COVID-19 recovery cases in the continent. Africa CDC said this in a tweet on its official Twitter account @AfricaCDC on Tuesday morning. “#COVID19 – UPDATE: MARCH 31 2020 – 10:00 am EAT,” Africa CDC tweeted. “African Union Member States (47) reporting COVID-19 cases (5,255), deaths (172), and recoveries (371) by region.” DAILY POST recalls that the Coronavirus death cases in Africa as of Sunday, March 29 was 134.